<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1589524-do-you-need-to-read-the-series-in-order">Do you need to read the series in order?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1589524'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F30068.The_Book_of_the_Dead">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1589524-do-you-need-to-read-the-series-in-order">2 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1589524-do-you-need-to-read-the-series-in-order">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/75065591-jason-monroe"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1548903596i/75065591._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/75065591-jason-monroe">Jason Monroe</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The first two books in the series, Relic and Reliquary, do introduce some mainstay characters, but don&apos;t really give much background to Agent Penderga<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The first two books in the series, Relic and Reliquary, do introduce some mainstay characters, but don't really give much background to Agent Pendergast. I feel like he is not the main character in these two, just more of a leading character. Book #3, The Cabinet of Curiosities, is where you really start learning more about him and his background. I feel this is where he becomes the main character of the series and it starts to become about him. I would highly suggest starting to read them in order from The Cabinet of Curiosities.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link1053974" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=1053974&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F1589524-do-you-need-to-read-the-series-in-order%2Fanswers%2F1053974-the-first-two-books-in">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
</ul>

