<span id="freeTextContainer13034999828304951196">4.5 stars. How do people dream this stuff up?? I just can&apos;t imagine coming up with this even in a drug induced hallucination of epic proportions. That&apos;s the thing, this third (and final?) book in the Diogenes trilogy is a story of epic proportions. Its like the ads that annoy the shit out of me on the TV where they yell at you to buy useless gadgets with a sales pitch that goes: &apos;and what about this...and this.. but wait, there&apos;s more...and a set of steak knives&apos;. Douglas Preston has thrown ever</span>
  <span id="freeText13034999828304951196" style="display:none">4.5 stars. How do people dream this stuff up?? I just can't imagine coming up with this even in a drug induced hallucination of epic proportions. That's the thing, this third (and final?) book in the Diogenes trilogy is a story of epic proportions. Its like the ads that annoy the shit out of me on the TV where they yell at you to buy useless gadgets with a sales pitch that goes: 'and what about this...and this.. but wait, there's more...and a set of steak knives'. Douglas Preston has thrown everything at this story, but somehow it all works and hangs together. Pendergast in prison, WTF? And don't get me started on the Senef tomb exhibition. Just read the story. No, read the trilogy. My mind is still popping with the complexities. I was just thinking about how boring some the titles currently on my Kindle app sound and I had a thought - what about another Pendergast book??? Yes, she cried!</span>
  <a data-text-id="13034999828304951196" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

